The paper deals with error-correcting codes and their properties, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CC) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the concept of local testing, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper uses algebraic techniques to study the codes, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
